        <description>
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Unit Conversion Reference Overview</title>
                <para>
                    This Data Module provides comprehensive unit conversion tables and precision 
                    rules for the AMPEL360 Q100 program. It ensures consistent unit usage across 
                    technical documentation, with emphasis on hydrogen-specific measurements and 
                    SI/Imperial conversions commonly required in aerospace applications.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Purpose:</emphasis> To provide quick reference 
                    for unit conversions, eliminate conversion errors, and standardize precision 
                    and rounding practices.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Primary Unit System:</emphasis> SI (International 
                    System of Units) is the primary unit system. Imperial/US customary units are 
                    provided as secondary reference where industry practice requires.
                </para>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <levelledPara>
                <title>SI Base Units and Derived Units</title>
                <para>
                    The Q100 program uses the following SI base units:
                </para>
                <table>
                    <tgroup cols="4">
                        <thead>
                            <row>
                                <entry>Quantity</entry>
                                <entry>Unit Name</entry>
                                <entry>Symbol</entry>
                                <entry>Typical Application</entry>
                            </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry>Length</entry>
                                <entry>meter</entry>
                                <entry>m</entry>
                                <entry>Dimensions, distances</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>Mass</entry>
                                <entry>kilogram</entry>
                                <entry>kg</entry>
                                <entry>Weight, fuel load</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>Time</entry>
                                <entry>second</entry>
                                <entry>s</entry>
                                <entry>Duration, rates</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>Temperature</entry>
                                <entry>kelvin</entry>
                                <entry>K</entry>
                                <entry>Cryogenic temperatures</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>Electric Current</entry>
                                <entry>ampere</entry>
                                <entry>A</entry>
                                <entry>Electrical systems</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>Amount of Substance</entry>
                                <entry>mole</entry>
                                <entry>mol</entry>
                                <entry>Chemical calculations</entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Length Conversions</title>
                <table>
                    <tgroup cols="3">
                        <thead>
                            <row>
                                <entry>From</entry>
                                <entry>To</entry>
                                <entry>Multiply by</entry>
                            </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry>meters (m)</entry>
                                <entry>feet (ft)</entry>
                                <entry>3.28084</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>feet (ft)</entry>
                                <entry>meters (m)</entry>
                                <entry>0.3048</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>meters (m)</entry>
                                <entry>inches (in)</entry>
                                <entry>39.3701</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>inches (in)</entry>
                                <entry>meters (m)</entry>
                                <entry>0.0254</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>millimeters (mm)</entry>
                                <entry>inches (in)</entry>
                                <entry>0.0393701</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>inches (in)</entry>
                                <entry>millimeters (mm)</entry>
                                <entry>25.4</entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Precision:</emphasis> Round to 2 decimal places 
                    for dimensions over 1m, 1 decimal place for dimensions under 1m, 0 decimal 
                    places for rough approximations.
                </para>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Mass Conversions</title>
                <table>
                    <tgroup cols="3">
